Experimental Design

This experiment was set up to examine the expression of Gat201 in different strains grown under the same conditions.

Strains: H99, KN99-alpha (KNa), Madhani-Gat201 deletion mutant (M-Gat201) and 2 Gat201 complemented strains (into Madhani-Gat201 deletion strain) C26 and C30.

Culture conditions: Set up overnight cultures from a single colony in YPD at 30 degrees, 150rpm, 2 biological replicates. Cultures were set up in 20 ml RPMI at an OD of 0.1 from the ON culture. Cell were washed with RPMI prior to testing the OD and setting up cultures in RPMI. Cultures were incubated at 37 degrees, 150rpm for 7 hours.

Sample collection: 19 ml Samples were collected at 6 hours. Samples were fixed in methanol on dry ice for 3-5 mins. My Cryptococcus RNA extraction protocol was followed to isolate RNA from samples.The samples were NOT lyophilise due to timr constraints.

Replicates: 3 biological replicates were collected for each sample. 3 technical replicates +RT and 1 -RT

Test Primers: Gat201 CNAG_01551 (set 1) Gat201 CNAG_06762 (Set 1) Liv 3 CNAG_05835 (Set 1)

Reference gene primers: CNAG_04994 (SRP14) CNAG_00483 (ACT1) CNAG_00121 (GDP1)

Split Sample column into BioRep, Time, Condition

plate_sep <- separate(plate, 
         sample_id, 
         into = c("Sample" , "BioRep"), 
         sep = "-", 
         remove = FALSE)
view(plate_sep)

Plot all reps, unnormalized

ggplot(data = plate_sep) +
  geom_point(aes(x = target_id, y = cq, shape = prep_type, colour = target_id),
    position = position_jitter(width = 0.2, height = 0)
  ) +
  labs(
    y = "Quantification cycle (Cq)",
    title = "All reps, unnormalized"
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~sample_id) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5))

Normalise data with 3 reference genes

plate_norm <- plate_sep %>%
  group_by(sample_id)%>%
  filter(prep_type == "+RT" )%>%
  calculate_deltacq_bysampleid(ref_target_ids = c("SRP14", "ACT1", "GDP1"))
